msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:74
msgid ""
"Linux kernel virtual TPM frontend driver. This driver provides vTPM access "
"to a Linux-based DomU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:77
msgid "mini-os/tpmback:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:78
msgid ""
"Mini-os TPM backend driver. The Linux frontend driver connects to this "
"backend driver to facilitate communications between the Linux DomU and its "
"vTPM. This driver is also used by vtpmmgr-stubdom to communicate with vtpm-"
"stubdom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:83
msgid "vtpm-stubdom:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:84
msgid ""
"A mini-os stub domain that implements a vTPM. There is a one to one mapping "
"between running vtpm-stubdom instances and logical vtpms on the system. The "
"vTPM Platform Configuration Registers (PCRs) are normally all initialized to "
"zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:89
msgid "mini-os/tpmfront:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:90
msgid ""
"Mini-os TPM frontend driver. The vTPM mini-os domain vtpm-stubdom uses this "
"driver to communicate with vtpmmgr-stubdom. This driver is also used in mini-"
"os domains such as pv-grub that talk to the vTPM domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:95
msgid "vtpmmgr-stubdom:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:96
msgid ""
"A mini-os domain that implements the vTPM manager. There is only one vTPM "
"manager and it should be running during the entire lifetime of the machine.  "
"This domain regulates access to the physical TPM on the system and secures "
"the persistent state of each vTPM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:102
msgid "mini-os/tpm_tis:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/xen-tpmfront.rst:103
msgid ""
"Mini-os TPM version 1.2 TPM Interface Specification (TIS) driver. This "
"driver used by vtpmmgr-stubdom to talk directly to the hardware TPM. "
"Communication is facilitated by mapping hardware memory pages into vtpmmgr-"
"stubdom."
msgstr ""

